<p>only with the addition of a red arm band (&amp; a guard with fixed bayonets). Managed to acquire a few Boches sausages.<br/>Everything is going smoothly &ndash; not many patients coming in which is just as well as the men are hard at work getting the place in decent shape.<br/>We can hear the boom of big gun fire to-day; evidently the British fleet is bombarding the Belgian coast about 30 miles to the north.<br/>10th July 1916 (Mond. 8a.m.). :-<br/>Yesterday afternoon I managed to get into Boulogne for the first time. Went in by tram (fare 25 cent.) &ndash; bought a couple of guides, dictionary, papers etc. and then walked back to camp &ndash; about 4 kilom&egrave;tres. It was a lovely afternoon and being Sunday everyone could take advantage of it by getting out in the open. The view from</p>
